-- Alliot-Marie Sees Duty to Be Ready If Named Prime Minister, Le Figaro Says
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-11T05:14:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/alliot-marie-sees-duty-to-be-ready-if-named-prime-minister-le-figaro-says.html
French Justice Minister Michele
Alliot-Marie told Le Figaro in an interview that she considers
it her duty to be ready to serve as prime minister if asked to
do so by President Nicolas Sarkozy.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
